    "content_hash": "51a23201a907e85a",
    "department": "Enterprise",
    "description": "About the Role:\n\nAs an Engineer II -System validation Test Automation, you will work closely with senior engineers to validate NETGEAR’s Insight along with Wireless Access points, Pro Routers, Switches and Security Devices. You will be responsible for testing both functional and performance aspects of networking and wireless features. You will contribute to our automation efforts using Python and Robot Framework and help integrate these tests into continuous delivery pipelines.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n - Design and execute test cases for either of Switches, Pro Routers, Access Points, and Security Devices running advanced wireless and network features.\n\n - Validate wireless networking features including 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/ax/be, roaming, band steering, DFS, and mesh technologies.\n\n - Test and debug issues related to wireless security protocols (WPA2, WPA3), firewall behavior, VPN, and access control.\n\n - Validate wired/wireless interoperability across Layer 2/3 switches, routers, and end-user devices.\n\n - Develop and maintain automation test scripts using Python and Robot Framework.\n\n - Work with senior QA and development engineers to debug and reproduce issues.\n\n - Track defects using Jira, maintain test documentation in Confluence, and manage scripts in Git/GitHub.\n\n - Execute tests in simulated/Real environments with real Switches, access points, clients, and security gateways.\n\n - Participate in Agile activities and collaborate across cross-functional teams (embedded, cloud, cross functional QA).\n\nQualifications:\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Electronics, Telecommunications, or a related field.\n\n - 2-4 years of experience in QA/testing or networking\n\n - Strong interest or certification in Networking/Wi-Fi (e.g., CCNA, CWNA) is a plus.\n\n - Strong desire to grow in the field of networking technologies and QA automation.\n\nTechnical Skills:\n\n - Wireless Networking:\n   \n   - Understanding of 802.11 standards (a/b/g/n/ac/ax/be), Familiarity with Wi-Fi security protocols (WEP, WPA2, WPA3)\n   \n   - Concepts like SSID, channel bonding, MIMO, OFDMA, beamforming, Roaming, Mesh Wi-Fi, and AP/client interaction\n   \n   - Hands-on with wireless technology and enterprise APs and Switches preferred\n\n - Networking:\n   \n   - Knowledge on TCP/IP, VLANs, DHCP, NAT, DNS, Routing, Switching (L2/L3)\n   \n   - validating Pro Routers, Access Points, and firewall/VPN configurations is plus\n\n - Automation \u0026 Programming:\n   \n   - Proficient in Python scripting\n   \n   - Familiarity with Robot Framework\n   \n   - Exposure to Java, SQL, or Selenium is a plus\n\n - Tools \u0026 Platforms:\n   \n   - Jenkins, Jira, Git, GitHub, Confluence\n   \n   - MySQL, HTML, CSS\n   \n   - Test/development on Linux, Windows, and embedded environments\n\n - Computer Science Fundamentals:\n   \n   - Data Structures, Algorithms, OOP\n   \n   - Debugging and log analysis\n\nCompany Statement/Values:  \n\nAt NETGEAR, we are on a mission to unleash the full potential of connectivity with intelligent solutions that delight and protect. We turn ideas into innovative networking products that connect people, power businesses, and advance the way we live.  \n\nWe're a performance-driven, talented and connected team that's committed to delivering world-class products for our customers. As a company, we value our employees as the most essential building blocks of our success. And as teammates, we commit to taking our work to the Next Gear by living our values: we Dare to Transform the future, Connect and Delight our customers, Communicate Courageously with each other and collaborate to Win It Together. You’ll find our values woven through our processes, present in our decisions, and celebrated throughout our culture. \n\nWe strive to attract top talent and create a great workplace where people feel engaged, inspired, challenged, proud and respected. If you are creative, forward-thinking, passionate about technology and are looking for a rewarding career to make an impact, then you've got what it takes to succeed at NETGEAR. Join our network and help us shape the future of connectivity. \n\nNETGEAR hires based on merit. All qualified applicants will receive equal consideration for employment. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.",
